# Task 0002: Agent Bootstrap — Task Watcher

## Objective
Implement a simple task watcher script (`watcher.py`) that continuously monitors the `TASKS/` directory for new work.

## Requirements
- **Script**: `watcher.py` in the project root
- **Polling interval**: Check `TASKS/` every 60 seconds
- **Detection**: Identify pending `.md` files (ignore `.md.done`)
- **Logging**: Log all activity (scans, discoveries, errors) to `LOGS/watcher.log`
- **Automation-ready**: Clean daemon-style loop, signal handling for graceful shutdown
- **Python implementation**, modular and extensible

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] `watcher.py` runs continuously and polls `TASKS/` every 60 seconds
- [ ] New `.md` task files are detected and logged
- [ ] Activity is written to `LOGS/watcher.log`
- [ ] Graceful shutdown on SIGINT/SIGTERM
- [ ] Script is ready to be extended with task execution hooks
